Package com.intellij.execution.configurations

Interface RunConfiguration

  • All Superinterfaces:
    java.lang.Cloneable, RunProfile
    All Known Subinterfaces:
    DebugAwareConfiguration, DebuggableRunConfiguration, InputRedirectAware, LocatableConfiguration, ModuleRunConfiguration, PersistentAwareRunConfiguration, RunConfigurationWithRunnerSettings
    All Known Implementing Classes:
    AbstractPythonLegacyTestRunConfiguration, AbstractPythonRunConfiguration, AbstractPythonTestRunConfiguration, AbstractRunConfiguration, AbstractServerPythonRunConfiguration, AntRunConfiguration, ApplicationConfiguration, DeployToServerRunConfiguration, DocutilsRunConfiguration, ExternalSystemRunConfiguration, GradleRunConfiguration, GroovyScriptRunConfiguration, JarApplicationConfiguration, JavaScratchConfiguration, JavaTestConfigurationBase, JavaTestConfigurationWithDiscoverySupport, JUnitConfiguration, LocatableConfigurationBase, ModuleBasedConfiguration, MvcRunConfiguration, PyTestRunConfiguration, PythonDocTestRunConfiguration, PythonNoseTestRunConfiguration, PythonRunConfiguration, PythonUnitTestRunConfiguration, PyToxConfiguration, RemoteConfiguration, RemoteDebugConfiguration, RestRunConfiguration, RunConfigurationBase, RuntimeConfiguration, RuntimeConfigurationProducer.DelegatingRuntimeConfiguration, ShRunConfiguration, SphinxRunConfiguration, UnknownRunConfiguration, XsltRunConfiguration

    public interface RunConfiguration
extends RunProfile, java.lang.Cloneable
    A run configuration which can be managed by a user and displayed in the UI.

    If debugger is provided by plugin, it should also implement RunConfigurationWithSuppressedDefaultDebugAction. Otherwise (in case of disabled plugin) debug action may be enabled in UI but with no reaction.

    See Also:
    com.intellij.execution.RunManager, RunConfigurationBase, RefactoringListenerProvider, RunConfigurationExtensionBase

If additional control over validation is required, the object returned from this method may also implement CheckableRunConfigurationEditor. The returned object can also implement SettingsEditorGroup if the settings it provides need to be displayed in multiple tabs.

      • hideDisabledExecutorButtons

        default boolean hideDisabledExecutorButtons()
        If this method returns true, disabled executor buttons (e.g. Run) will be hidden when this configuration is selected. Note that this will lead to UI flickering when switching between this configuration and others for which this property is false, so you should avoid overriding this method unless you're really sure of what you're doing.

      • checkConfiguration

        default void checkConfiguration()
                         throws RuntimeConfigurationException
        Checks whether the run configuration settings are valid. Note that this check may be invoked on every change (i.e. after each character typed in an input field).
        Throws:
        RuntimeConfigurationException - if the configuration settings contain a non-fatal problem which the user should be warned about but the execution should still be allowed.
        RuntimeConfigurationError - if the configuration settings contain a fatal problem which makes it impossible to execute the run configuration.
